  "name": "Morrison COU2 — VAD hemolysis credibility assessment (Minimal Profile)",
  "description": "This model has been applied in clinical research settings to predict hemolysis in centrifugal blood pumps under ventricular assist device operating conditions. The CFD hemolysis model targets the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump geometry and evaluates absolute hemolysis indices across a range of flow rates and rotational speeds representative of VAD therapy. Monte Carlo uncertainty quantification was performed over inlet boundary conditions and rheological parameters. All 13 ASME V&V 40 credibility factors were reviewed; seven were formally assessed and six were flagged as epistemic gaps at Model Risk Level 5. Despite gaps, the aggregate evidence was judged sufficient for the intended low-risk regulatory submission context, and the assessment was accepted. No structured Context of Use object is provided in this minimal-profile submission; intended-use scope is conveyed only through this narrative.",
  "bindsRequirement": "https://uofa.net/synth/req/vad-hemolysis-mrl5-req-001",
  "bindsClaim": "https://uofa.net/synth/claim/vad-hemolysis-cfd-credibility-claim",
  "bindsModel": "https://uofa.net/synth/model/cfd-hemolysis-centrifugal-pump-v3",
  "bindsDataset": [
    "https://uofa.net/synth/data/fda-pump-piv-experimental-dataset",
    "https://uofa.net/synth/data/vad-hemolysis-monte-carlo-outputs"
  ],
